main event: An unidentified object emitting white light with blue and green colors was observed via ground radar in North Dakota for 15 minutes on July 30, 1958.
interesting points: The object traveled at a moderate speed and had an undetermined shape., The sighting was documented in Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program., The planet Venus was concluded to be in the location at the time of the sighting, but the object was not definitively identified., A patrolman corroborated the observation with an identical report., There was insufficient data to ascertain the nature of the object as it could have been an aircraft, balloon, or space vehicle.
sighted object: unidentified object emitting white light with blue and green colors
witness description: Wallace Harold and Patrolman Fron Tieger, both from North Dakota
